  *** KEY INSIGHT ***
  The simple formula H(T1)*H(T2)^|V1| counts only BLOCK paths
  (where each group is visited contiguously).
  But the cyclic T1 = 3-cycle allows interleaving: visiting
  part of group A, then group B, then back to group A.
  This creates 42 extra paths beyond the 3 block paths!
  Total: 3 + 42 = 45 = 45.

