======================================================================
PART 3: TRANSFER MATRIX FOR LEX PRODUCT
  Define states as (group, position_within_group)
  The transfer matrix M[s1, s2] = 1 iff transition s1->s2 is an arc
  H = #{Ham paths in M} = same as our tournament
======================================================================

  Block structure of adjacency matrix:
    M[group 0 -> group 0] = [[0, 1], [0, 0]]
    M[group 0 -> group 1] = [[1, 1], [1, 1]]
    M[group 0 -> group 2] = [[0, 0], [0, 0]]
    M[group 1 -> group 0] = [[0, 0], [0, 0]]
    M[group 1 -> group 1] = [[0, 1], [0, 0]]
    M[group 1 -> group 2] = [[1, 1], [1, 1]]
    M[group 2 -> group 0] = [[1, 1], [1, 1]]
    M[group 2 -> group 1] = [[0, 0], [0, 0]]
    M[group 2 -> group 2] = [[0, 1], [0, 0]]

  Cross-group blocks are ALL-ONES for winning direction,
  ALL-ZEROS for losing direction. This creates maximum flexibility
  for path construction, explaining the high H value.

